abstract: The number of troops injured has steadily increased since the Jan. 8 attack.
snippet: The number of troops injured has steadily increased since the Jan. 8 attack.
lead_paragraph: More than 100 American service members have traumatic brain injuries from Iranian airstrikes on Al Asad Air Base in Iraq in January, the Defense Department said, a number that was more than 50 percent higher than previously disclosed.

abstract: He pretended to be different. He was lying.
snippet: He pretended to be different. He was lying.
lead_paragraph: One thing many people forget about the 2016 election is that as a candidate, Donald Trump promised to be a different kind of Republican. Unlike the mainstream of his party, he declared, he would raise taxes on the rich and wouldn’t cut programs like Social Security, Medicare and Medicaid that ordinary Americans rely on. At the same time, he would invest large sums in rebuilding America’s infrastructure.

abstract: The Pentagon said it “strongly opposes” the request from the internet giant, which is challenging the awarding of a defense contract to Microsoft.
snippet: The Pentagon said it “strongly opposes” the request from the internet giant, which is challenging the awarding of a defense contract to Microsoft.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Amazon has asked a federal court to let it depose President Trump and Defense Secretary Mark Esper, arguing that hearing from them is essential to determining if they intervened against the internet company when the Pentagon awarded a multibillion-dollar contract to a competitor.

abstract: Workers can’t return to their jobs as supply lines get snarled, extending the forced holiday and fracturing the country.
snippet: Workers can’t return to their jobs as supply lines get snarled, extending the forced holiday and fracturing the country.
lead_paragraph: Workers are stuck in their hometowns. Officials want detailed health plans before factories or offices can reopen. Assembly lines that make General Motors cars and Apple iPhones are standing silent.

headline_main: ‘Like Europe in Medieval Times’: Virus Slows China’s Economy
headline_print_headline: Virus Lockdown  Stifles Economy  In a Wary China

abstract: Many of the world’s biggest epidemics have been traced to China. But contagion does not play geographical favorites and the country has made great strides in public health.

abstract: The budget, while largely a messaging document, reflects the administration’s spending priorities’ stark contrast with the president’s Democratic rivals.
snippet: The budget, while largely a messaging document, reflects the administration’s spending priorities’ stark contrast with the president’s Democratic rivals.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump released a $4.8 trillion budget proposal on Monday that includes a familiar list of deep cuts to student loan assistance, affordable housing efforts, food stamps and Medicaid, reflecting Mr. Trump’s election-year effort to continue shrinking the federal safety net.
